# S04 — ARCHITECT Brief: Tuya Integration

role: ARCHITECT
sprint: S04
objective: Extend S03 design to support Tuya without duplication

design-focus:
  - Provider abstraction: Tuya client alongside eWeLink
  - Shared Device model: both providers normalize to same schema
  - Unified device registry (server aggregates eWeLink + Tuya)
  - Optional: Provider-agnostic "smart device" facade

patterns:
  - Adapter: TuyaAdapter implements same interface as EweLinkAdapter
  - Factory or registry: resolve provider by device type/source
  - Single API: GET /devices returns combined list with source tag

layer-boundaries:
  - Backend: Tuya client service, device normalization (match eWeLink schema)
  - Frontend: Reuse DeviceCard; add Tuya section or unified list
  - No Tuya SDK in client; all via API/socket

decisions-to-document:
  - Tuya device schema mapping to shared Device model
  - API shape for Tuya control (scenes, energy)
  - Socket event extension (ewelink:update, tuya:update or unified)
